    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the socioeconomic part, but if you look at raw FBI ucr data or arrest statistics, there are still very clear disparities in certain demographics. even if those are \"explained\" by other things, how do researchers account for the fact that the raw numbers show such a massive gap? some people argue that the statistical deviation itself is a biological or cultural indicator rather than just a result of poverty. what does the literature say about those specific arguments?",
